Vuln 2: Unauthenticated Agents Service API: apps/agents/src/api/routes.py
Severity: High

Confidence: 8/10

Category: missing_authentication / unauthorized_access

Description: The agents microservice exposes three endpoints with no authentication whatsoever — no Bearer token validation, no API key guard, no dependency injection security:

POST /api/v1/agents/execute
POST /api/v1/agents/execute/stream
POST /api/v1/agents/validate
The service is also bound to port 8000 on the host machine (per docker-compose.yml), making it reachable beyond the internal Docker network. The Gateway adds authentication before forwarding to this service, but this is not a security boundary — it only applies to requests routed through the Gateway.

Exploit Scenario: An attacker with access to port 8000 (e.g., on the same host, same Docker network via lateral movement from another compromised container, or in any environment where the port is inadvertently exposed) can call these endpoints directly, bypassing Gateway authentication entirely. The request body accepts attacker-controlled fields including system_prompt, tools, credentials (OAuth tokens), and agent_tool_instances. This allows unauthorized LLM execution, credential theft from tool configurations, and unauthorized operations on connected third-party services (Google Calendar, HubSpot, etc.).

